      About this item

      • WIDE RANGE OF APPLICATIONS : The wireless weather resistant driveway alarm motion sensor can be used to monitor&protect your outdoor/indoor property. Such as driveway, front porch, gate,pool,garage,shed and etc. Great for home, business,and office.The sensor will work properly at all the seasons. Working temperature range from -30 to 150 degree Fahrenheit.
      • 1/2 MILE LONG WIRELESS TRANSMISSION RANGE : Both the motion sensor and plug-in receiver pick up alarm signals up to 1/2 mile away(actual range will vary depending on the local terrain), it is a great solution even you have a large perimeter or property to monitor. The system adopts improved wireless transmission technology(FSK+FHSS) to avoid the wireless signal interference from other devices.
      • 50-FT WIDE MOTION DETECTION RANGE : The motion sensor will detect moving people or vehicles from 35 feet to 50 feet in front of it. Improved motion detection chip and detection angle to reduce the false alarms from dead leaves/small animals/sunlight/wind/temperature changes and etc. It has 2 adjustable sensitivities( Low=35ft; High=50ft), ideal for driveways, walking paths,yard,garage,gate,pool and anywhere of your outdoor/indoor property you want to be alerted.
      • PLUG&PLAY,SUPER EASY TO INSTALL : Power on the motion sensor by 3pcs AA 1.5V Alkaline batteries(the package does not include the batteries) and plug the receiver into the outlet,here we go. The unit has been programmed before shipped, place the sensors to walls, fence posts, trees, or any other surface,the installation time can be as little as a few minutes.
      • FULLY EXPANDBLE SYSTEM - The unit includes one plug-in receiver and two motion sensors. Expandable up to 32 sensors and unlimited receivers for complete coverage of your outdoor/indoor property. 4 volume levels adjustment and 35 optional melodies. Match different melody with different sensors around your property to differentiate where motion is being detected.

      Product Description

      HTZSAFE Wireless Alarms: The HTZSAFE wireless driveway alarm system alerts you at anytime the weather resistant outdoor/indoor sensor detects motion from people, vehicles or large animals.

      -- The sensor is powered by 3pcs AA 1.5V Alkaline batteries( the package does not include the batteries). Monitor/protect your outdoor/indoor property all the day and night.

      -- The sensor is weather resistant, will work properly at all the seasons. Working temperature range from -30 to 150 degree Fahrenheit.

      -- Up to 1/2 mile long wireless transmission range(ideal conditions),it is a great solution even to monitor the long driveway/large property/and etc; --Up to 50FT wide sensor detection range and 2 adjustable sensitivities(High=50ft;Low=35ft),ideal for driveways, walking paths,yard,garage,gate,pool and anywhere of your outdoor/indoor property you want to be alerted.

      -- Improved wireless transmission technology(FSK+FHSS) to avoid the signal interference from other wireless devices.

      -- Plug-in receiver has 4 adjustable volume levels and 35 optional melodies, match different melody with different sensor around your property to differentiate where motion is being detected.

      -- Fully expandable system, up to 32 HTZSAFE sensors can be added to the receiver and 1 sensor can be added to unlimited receivers. -- Restart the receivers or sensors will not miss the records.

      -- HTZSAFE focus on developing Wireless Alarms more than 20 years, HTZSAFE has several kinds of transmitters and receivers which have different functions for different application and environment,and all the HTZSAFE products can work together.

      Mailbox Alert

      Notify you when the mailbox be opened.

      Adjust the installation height and the detection angle to avoid the small animals to activate the sensor.

      Alert you if anyone enters your property without your knowledge.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      5 out of 5 stars
      Really like my motion sensors !
      I purchased five of these already. Something I have noticed is that the sensor has been upgraded. The older version had no vent or drain, the new version does have a rubber plug that is vented. I used clear silicone on the seals, drilled a drain hole on bottom of the older version, and mount them with a clear plastic shroud (Dollar Store)to better protect them from the rain.I cannot say whether they will cover a 1/2 mile distance but they work very well at 800 plus feet out to my back fence corners, and that is through the heavily brushed trees to the interior of my home. The alert is very loud and will get your attention. I use them on my trails for game and small animals. They just work like they're supposed to. I will add to or update my review as time permits.

        Reviewed in the United States on March 3, 2025
        Color: 1 Receiver+ 2 SensorVerified Purchase
        Recommended. Long battery life, 3aa lasted about 18 months before needing replaced. Stood up to weather in Ohio. Transmitter is mounted on a metal fence post so it is out in the elements and no issues. It's mounted about 50 feet away from the receiver. The volume on the receiver is plenty loud and can be adjusted down. Easy to set up and adjust. Discreet enough to blend in, yet could be mistaken for a camera if a burglar notices it. More affordable than some similar alarms and a good value all around. Never needed tech support, but there's a sticker on the receiver with the contact info just in case. If you lose power or unplug the receiver, you'll have to readjust the receiver to your alarm of choice, which takes only about 30 seconds. The verbal alarm voice sounds like an Asian female. The doorbell and other non verbal type alarms sound perfectly fine, not too synthetic. But the speaker is tiny, so the quality the sound is average, but still perfectly fine. I'll be buying an additional transmitter for the side yard in the spring.

        5.0 out of 5 stars Very Awesome Product!!!
        Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2025
        Color: 1 Receiver + 3 SensorVerified Purchase
        These little security owls are my new best friends! I've only had them for a few weeks but...they are working consistently and holding up in rain, snow and heavy frost. The sensors are advertised to have a max effective range of 50 feet, it's more like 70 feet. So easy to set up, plenty of available alarm sounds to choose from. The in house alarm sounding unit has an adjustable volume level and it's real good. Have had nasty freezing rain and snow hitting these sensors, the design of the housing protects the seeing eye really well from the elements and drains away water from the sensor, well thought out design! The mounts are real easy to screw in to trees or siding. Swivels are real good too. I like that they are battery and not solar powered. This enables placement to be in shaded locations. Also, good that the sensors use three double A batteries. Plenty of battery power. The build is with heavy duty plastic, made well. The value for the money is surprisingly good. A few learnings to share; big wind triggers sensors by moving large tree limbs, small trees, brush, etc. squirrels sat on a couple sensors and bent them down, need to check and readjust as needed. Heavy snow bends spruce limbs down in front of sensor, check and clean snow off or trim branches as necessary.

      • AM
        4.0 out of 5 stars Really Nice Alert System
        Reviewed in the United States on June 20, 2024
        Color: 1 Receiver + 3 SensorVerified Purchase
        I ordered this to warn me of persons who come up my driveway and approach my vehicles, especially at night as my neighborhood has had a few instances of residents cars getting broken into in the early morning hours. Since I was ordering I decided to order the pack that came with the 3 sensors so that besides the driveway I could put up a sensor to cover the access point to my sheds and the side of my house. Upon receiving it I immediately read the instructions and set up the units. I was amazed how easy it was to set them up for use. The 3 sensors came already electronically paired with the receiver so all I had to do was install the batteries and choose an alarm sound for each sensor. This was done simply by activating each sensor and pushing the "chime" button until I found a alert chime that I wanted to use for that sensor. Once an alert chime was locked in it was all set to go. I even checked the alarm chime setting by unplugging the receiver unit and then plugging it back in again to make sure my alert chime choices stayed programmed into the receiver....... I was pleased to discover the receiver did in fact keep my alarm chime choices even after being uplugged and then plugged in again. I then went outside and installed all 3 sensors units in their respective locations and I then tested them from every approach out to 50 feet. The sensors activated every single time and the receiver immediately chimed the alert sound I had chosen for each sensor. 2 of the sensors are within 100 feet of where I have the receiver but the 3rd sensor is placed way at the back of my property, about 175 feet, and all 3 sensors send a strong signal with each activation that immediately activates the receiver unit. I am really impressed with this system. The sensor units are small and dark colored (black), which I like because once installed they are difficult to see unless you know what to look for and exactly where to look. Each sensor comes with a nice mounting plate that screws onto the back of the sensor. The mount has a "socket ball" type attachment where it snaps securely into the base (that is attached to a tree, fence, etc) and this allows you to rotate the sensor up, down, side to side or to any angle you want it at. It works really well and keep the sensor securely aimed where you set it. The unit says that it's waterproof/resistant and while it does appear that it should be weather proof I had read one review where the consumer installed electrical tape over the seams just to be sure it would repel water..... this sounded like a good idea so I did the same thing and I am now very confident it will handle wet weather well. This system really is nice and really does work well. The other nice thing is that you can easily add more sensors in the future if you decide you need them. It also signals you when the batteries are getting low and needs to be replaced. Each sensor uses 3 AA batteries so they should last a long time if you use quality batteries. The only reason I only rated it 4 stars rather than 5 is simply because I need to see how it holds up and operates over time. After using the system for a while I will come back and update my review. But all in all I'm very happy with this system and how it functions.
